ere is the correct and complete XAML-only implementation for setting the DisplayFormat in a specific column of a DevExpress dxg:GridControl:

Correct XAML Code:
xml
코드 복사
<dxg:GridControl ItemsSource="{Binding YourDataSource}">
    <dxg:GridControl.Columns>
        <!-- Define other columns -->

        <!-- Time Column -->
        <dxg:GridColumn FieldName="time123" Header="Time">
            <dxg:GridColumn.EditSettings>
                <dxe:DateEditSettings DisplayFormat="yy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss" />
            </dxg:GridColumn.EditSettings>
        </dxg:GridColumn>
        
    </dxg:GridControl.Columns>
</dxg:GridControl>
Key Details:
FieldName: Replace "time123" with the actual property name in your data source that represents a DateTime value.
DisplayFormat: The DisplayFormat="yy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss" ensures that the DateTime value is displayed in the desired format directly in the column.
Header: The Header property is used to define the column title displayed in the grid.
Why This Works
EditSettings: The EditSettings property allows you to define how the cell is displayed and edited. Using dxe:DateEditSettings, you can control the formatting for DateTime values.
DisplayFormat: This property formats the displayed value of the DateTime field without altering the underlying data.
If this still doesn't work, ensure the following:

The DevExpress namespaces are correctly added to your XAML:
xml
코드 복사
xmlns:dxg="http://schemas.devexpress.com/winfx/2008/xaml/grid"
xmlns:dxe="http://schemas.devexpress.com/winfx/2008/xaml/editors"